Note:
UNICODE_TABLES - Canonical Composition / Decomposition Tables

This file exports lookup tables that string_utils.runa consults when
performing Unicode normalization (NFC / NFD form conversion). The full
production tables are derived from UnicodeData.txt (UCD) and reach
~50 000 entries; populating them is its own subproject and lives behind
the v0.2.x stdlib milestone.

Two symbols this file MUST export so callers in string_utils.runa link:

  UNICODE_COMPOSITION_TABLE - pointer to a flat sorted array of
    {primary_codepoint:int32, secondary_codepoint:int32,
     composed_codepoint:int32, padding:int32} entries (16 bytes each).
    Binary search uses the (primary, secondary) pair to locate a
    composed codepoint.

  UNICODE_COMPOSITION_COUNT - number of entries in the table above.

Until the v0.2.x table generator lands, both symbols are zero. Callers
already null-check the table pointer and fall back to passing characters
through unchanged when the table is empty - see string_utils.runa around
line 3048 - so this stub keeps Unicode-aware code paths compilable and
linkable without changing observable behavior for ASCII input (which is
all stage1 and the bootstrap compiler ever sees).
:End Note

Note: Zero-initialized stubs. Real tables ship with v0.2.x.
Let UNICODE_COMPOSITION_TABLE be 0
Let UNICODE_COMPOSITION_COUNT be 0
